# OCP Capacity Reporter

A lightweight, repeatable node inventory and capacity reporting tool for OpenShift clusters.
Extracts node resource data from the OpenShift API, generates a formatted Excel report,
and distributes it via email to stakeholders.

-----

## Overview

This script queries OpenShift cluster nodes and Machine/MachineSet objects to produce
an accurate per-node inventory report including business unit ownership, node role,
provisioned CPU cores, and memory. Output is a formatted `.xlsx` file with green header
row, alternating row colors, auto-filters, and frozen header — ready for stakeholder distribution.

> **Note:** This script is currently run manually per cluster. Full automation via a
> scheduled CronJob with service account authentication and multi-cluster looping
> is planned for the next phase. See the [Automation Roadmap](#automation-roadmap) section.

-----

## Requirements

- Python 3.6+
- `oc` CLI in PATH and authenticated to the target cluster
- `openpyxl` Python library

```bash
python3 -m pip install openpyxl --user
```

-----

## Usage

### Basic run (current cluster context)

```bash
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py
```

### Override cluster name

```bash
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py --cluster-name ocpprod
```

### Custom output directory

```bash
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py --out /home/asuma/reports
```

### Append to existing report (multi-cluster)

```bash
# First cluster - creates the file
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py

# Subsequent clusters - appends to same file
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py --append
```

### Send report via email

```bash
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py --email user@cscglobal.com
```

### Send to multiple recipients

```bash
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py --email user1@cscglobal.com,user2@cscglobal.com,user3@cscglobal.com
```

### Full multi-cluster run with email

```bash
# Login and collect each cluster, append to same file
oc login --token=<token> --server=https://api.ocpuat.csc.local:6443
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py

oc login --token=<token> --server=https://api.ocpprod.csc.local:6443
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py --append

oc login --token=<token> --server=https://api.ocpcom.csc.local:6443
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py --append --email user1@cscglobal.com,user2@cscglobal.com
```

