## Output

### Files generated

```
reports/
  ocp-capacity-2026-04.csv    # Raw CSV (Excel-compatible)
  ocp-capacity-2026-04.xlsx   # Formatted Excel workbook
```

### Excel schema

|Column       |Description                          |
|-------------|-------------------------------------|
|Month        |Report month (MM)                    |
|Year         |Report year (YYYY)                   |
|Cluster      |Cluster name (e.g. ocpuat, ocpprod)  |
|business_unit|BU derived from node labels or name  |
|size         |Node size (large, medium, small, n/a)|
|Role         |compute, infra, or control           |
|node         |Full node hostname                   |
|Cores        |Provisioned vCPU cores               |
|Memory (GiB) |Provisioned memory in GiB            |
|OS           |RHCOS version string                 |
|Kernel       |Kernel version                       |
|Kubelet      |Kubelet version                      |
|MachineSet   |MachineSet name                      |

### Business unit derivation

BU is resolved in the following priority order:

1. Node label `cscglobal.com/chargeback.businessUnit`
1. Node label `cscglobal.com/owner.businessUnit`
1. Node label `machine.openshift.io/cluster-api-machineset` (parsed)
1. Node name segment (e.g. `ocpuat-7bqb4-cls-large-xxxxx` → `cls`)
1. Fallback: `shared`

Control plane nodes always resolve to `shared`.

### CPU and memory source

CPU and memory are sourced from `providerSpec.value` in the MachineSet or Machine
object (`vcpuSockets * vcpusPerSocket` and `memorySize`) — not from kernel-reported
node capacity. This ensures values match provisioned specs (e.g. `96 GiB`, `8 cores`)
rather than kernel-reserved figures (e.g. `94.2 GiB`).

Lookup priority:

1. Individual Machine object keyed by node name (covers control plane)
1. MachineSet object keyed by MachineSet name (covers compute/infra pools)
1. Fallback to node capacity if neither is found

