## Automation Roadmap

The following work is planned to fully automate this reporting process:

### Phase 1 — Service Account Setup (per cluster)

Create a read-only service account in each cluster:

```bash
oc create serviceaccount capacity-reporter -n default
oc adm policy add-cluster-role-to-user view -z capacity-reporter -n default
oc create token capacity-reporter -n default --duration=8760h
```

Store tokens in a cluster config file on the bastion:

```
~/.ocp-reporter/clusters.conf

# Format: clustername|api-url|token
ocpuat|https://api.ocpuat.csc.local:6443|<token>
ocpprod|https://api.ocpprod.csc.local:6443|<token>
ocpcom|https://api.ocpcom.csc.local:6443|<token>
ocpdev|https://api.ocpdev.csc.local:6443|<token>
```

### Phase 2 — Multi-cluster loop

Add `--clusters` flag to loop through all clusters automatically:

```bash
python3 ocp-capacity-report.py \
  --clusters-config ~/.ocp-reporter/clusters.conf \
  --email user1@cscglobal.com,user2@cscglobal.com
```

The script will login to each cluster, collect data, append to a single report,
and send one combined email at the end.

### Phase 3 — Scheduled CronJob

Deploy as a CronJob on a management bastion or OCP cluster running on the
1st of each month:

```bash
# /etc/cron.d/ocp-capacity-reporter
0 7 1 * * asuma /usr/bin/python3 /home/asuma/ocp-capacity-report.py \
  --clusters-config /home/asuma/.ocp-reporter/clusters.conf \
  --out /home/asuma/reports \
  --email user1@cscglobal.com,user2@cscglobal.com
```

Historical reports are retained in `~/reports/` with monthly filenames
(`ocp-capacity-YYYY-MM.xlsx`) for trend analysis.

